  "prompt": "Where can I found a large range of formal and evening wear in Gold Coast?",
  "response": "Okay, here's a breakdown of places to find a large range of formal and evening wear on the Gold Coast, categorized for easier browsing:\n\n**1. Department Stores (For Variety & Convenience):**\n\n*   **David Jones (Robina Town Centre & Pacific Fair):**\n    *   **Pros:** Offers a curated selection of Australian and international designers, often with a range of price points.  Good for finding classic and contemporary styles. You'll also find shoes and accessories.\n    *   **Cons:** Can be more expensive than other options.  Selection might be more focused on mainstream trends.\n*   **Myer (Pacific Fair):**\n    *   **Pros:** Similar to David Jones, but often with a more accessible price range.  They stock a variety of brands and styles, catering to a broader audience.\n    *   **Cons:** Can be very busy, especially on weekends. Quality can vary depending on the brand.\n\n**2. Boutiques & Specialist Stores (For Unique & Designer Options):**\n\n*   **Sajeela Keshav (Paradise Point):**\n    *   **Pros:** Known for luxurious fabrics, beautiful designs, and exceptional service. Offers a bespoke experience and high-end quality.\n    *   **Cons:** Likely to be the most expensive option on this list.\n*   **White Runway (Online with Gold Coast Showroom):**\n    *   **Pros:** Huge range of bridesmaid, formal, and evening dresses. Caters to various styles, sizes, and budgets. Often has sales and promotions.  The showroom allows you to try things on.\n    *   **Cons:** Can be overwhelming due to the sheer number of options.\n*   **Brides of Southport:**\n    *   **Pros:** Whilst the name says Brides, they carry a huge range of evening wear that would also suit formal occasions.\n    *   **Cons:** Can be more expensive than other options.\n*   **Various Boutiques in Marina Mirage:**\n    *   **Pros:** Marina Mirage houses a collection of upscale boutiques that often carry designer evening wear. Explore the shops individually.\n    *   **Cons:** Prices will generally be higher. Selection can be limited to specific designer aesthetics.\n*   **Browse Shopping Centres Like Pacific Fair & Robina Town Centre:**\n    *   **Pros:** These large shopping centres contain a mix of chain stores and smaller boutiques that may carry formal wear.  Worth dedicating time to browse.\n    *   **Cons:** Can be time-consuming to visit many different stores.\n\n**3. Dress Hire Options (For Cost-Effective & Trendy Choices):**\n\n*   **GlamCorner (Online with try-on options):**\n    *   **Pros:** Access to designer dresses for a fraction of the retail price.  Great for one-off events.  Wide range of styles and sizes.\n    *   **Cons:** Need to book in advance to ensure availability.  Need to be careful to avoid damage to the dress.\n*   **The Volte (Online - Gold Coast base):**\n    *   **Pros:** Similar to GlamCorner, another popular dress rental platform.  Can often find more unique or on-trend pieces.\n    *   **Cons:** Similar to GlamCorner, need to book in advance and be careful with the dress.\n\n**4. Outlet Shopping (For Discounted Finds):**\n\n*   **Harbour Town Premium Outlets:**\n    *   **Pros:** Can find discounted formal wear from various brands, including some Australian designers. Worth checking for end-of-season sales or clearance racks.\n    *   **Cons:** Selection can be limited and unpredictable.  Sizes may be restricted.\n\n**Tips for Your Shopping Trip:**\n\n*   **Set a Budget:**  Knowing your price range will help you narrow down your options and avoid overspending.\n*   **Consider the Event:**  Think about the dress code, the venue, and the overall style of the event.\n*   **Know Your Size:**  Get professionally measured to ensure you're shopping for the correct size.\n*   **Try On Multiple Styles:**  Don't be afraid to try on different silhouettes and fabrics to see what flatters your figure best.\n*   **Don't Forget Accessories:**  Shoes, jewelry, and a clutch can complete your look.\n*   **Read Reviews:**  If shopping online, read reviews from other customers to get an idea of the quality and fit of the dress.\n*   **Check Return Policies:**  Make sure you understand the return policy before making a purchase, especially if shopping online.\n*   **Factor in Alterations:**  Most dresses will require some alterations to fit perfectly.  Budget for this in your overall cost.\n*   **Book Appointments:** If you want personalised service, book appointments at smaller boutiques.\n\nGood luck with your dress search! Let me know if you have any other questions.\n",
